<subSubSection pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="73.[189,454,1247,1273]" box="[189,454,1247,1273]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,454,1247,1273]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,454,1247,1273]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="73.[189,1399,1295,1506]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,636,1295,1322]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuscula" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Montanocheila">
<emphasis box="[189,301,1295,1321]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[319,497,1295,1321]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Montanocheila</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[515,636,1295,1321]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">minuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[643,735,1296,1322]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has a similar structure of the male genitalia as the other members of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov" authorityYear="2002" box="[493,671,1332,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Montanocheila">
<emphasis box="[493,671,1332,1358]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Montanocheila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs strikingly in it’s small size and narrow body. From all members of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[497,654,1369,1396]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuscula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[497,654,1369,1396]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">C. minuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[661,752,1370,1396]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs by following characters: small size, eye pilose, face non-pilose, antennal pits separated, scutellum without bristles, male genitalia with gonopod (superior lobes) lacking a left process and with a well-developed right process. 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1028,1271,1443,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuscula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1028,1271,1443,1469]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Cheilosia minuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1278,1370,1443,1469]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is here tentatively placed in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov" authorityYear="2002" box="[652,830,1480,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Montanocheila">
<emphasis box="[652,830,1480,1506]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Montanocheila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="73.[189,324,1547,1573]" box="[189,324,1547,1573]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1547,1573]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1547,1573]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="73.[189,1398,1595,1658]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[654,776,1595,1621]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuscula">
<emphasis box="[654,776,1595,1621]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">minuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ meaning ‘small’, and refers to the small size if the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
